title: Matchsafe, "Nephrite and Gold with Monogram", ca. 1900
markings: FRANK HYAMS CO 128 NEW BOND ST W stamped on underside of lid's gold surround.
provenance: Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: Rectangular, slightly translucent nephrite box body and attatched lid, the bottom edge of lid has gold surround as does the upper edge of body. Lid is opened with nephrite cabochon release button. On box front is attached monogram "S". Gold link attached beneath gold hinge on left side. Striker carved into bottom with hatch marks.
